57.1	Color_Graphics_Adapter	Color Graphics Adapter	The Color Graphics Adapter , originally also called the Color/Graphics Adapter or IBM Color/Graphics Monitor Adapter, introduced in 1981, was IBM's first color graphics card, and the first color computer display standard for the IBM PC.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Arachne_CGA_Mode.png/320px-Arachne_CGA_Mode.png
